node.text: I’m grateful for the process it takes to build a strong bond with my dogs. I like when they make me earn it. When it takes several months of us challenging one another and figuring each other out. Hooch enjoyed seeing what he could get away with. He enjoys his freedom to do whatever he wants here, to be whoever he wants here. Sometimes I don’t think he even knows how good of a dog he is. The biggest part of his growth here has been his increase in confidence without the need of trying to be the Alpha. He needed to learn that he didn’t need to be the alpha in this family. There is no alpha, we are all one. We all are the pieces of each other that hold this pack together. We are so aligned now that we move in harmony. And hooch has been a major link to it all. The protector of the little dogs and the peace keeper of the large ones. I adore him, I’m so incredibly proud of him. I know it took a lot for him to trust me the way he does now but it didn’t take much for me to trust him. ❤️ #AdoptDontShop

node.text: All of us at @newlifeasherhouse are very excited to introduce you to Aries! Aries is a very special Ram to all of us and I have no doubt you will fall in love with him as soon as you meet, just like we did lol He has a very special vet appointment next week to get his horns trimmed because they are a bit to close to his beautiful cheeks :) Rams horns are crucial to their overall health! Not only to defend themselves but also to regulate their temperature and proper blood flow. Aries is a very special Ram who’s ass jiggles whenever you scratch his chin. So we have that in common already. I’m so so excited about the life we are going to provide for him. It will be filled with love, treats and ass jiggles.  Can’t wait for y’all to meet him and we can’t wait to meet y’all 🙏🏽❤️🐾 @newlifeasherhouse Please visit the link in bio or join our awesome patreon to support! Thanks so much and I hope you have an awesome weekend! Jiggle jiggle 😙

node.text: Outdoor naps in our new @llbean bed might be the best part about summer in Oregon.
